snippet.textDisplay: Consider how the largest mammals would have a more difficult time consuming more protein than natural for their species, which is the biggest contributing factor to this cell dysfunction in humans. They may also handle the resulting IGF-1 better when they are over fed, or maybe they just don't over feed for long enough periods to accumulate much cancer. They may accidentally fast frequently enough, which has been shown to help the body fight cancer. Not all cancers come from too much protein, it just seems that mammals are good destroying cancer cells when not bombarded with an unnatural amount of proteins.
